<br>
People keep bringing up the notion that it's not very roleplaying to have the TLC. Because it doesn't make sense for some item just to poof because someone of high level happens to kill the mob. Then they cite pen and paper games as an example.<br>
<br>
Well, consider this then. Would a DM in a pen and paper game pitch a high level party against some low level mobs? I'm going out on a limb and say no. No good DM would allow it. Unfortunately in a MMORPG there's no intelligent DM that would regulate this occurrence. <br>
<br>
The TLC is not the perfect rule to deal with this issue, but it's the best they can do without completely change all the mechanics of the game. <p>Thormiel Stormblade<BR>
